  "StockRole": "Garrison Unit",
  "YangsThoughts": "Originally developed by Luthien Armor Works as a cheap but durable garrison unit, the Kumazemi entered production after a brief test period showing promising results. Its name, meaning \"bear cicada\", is a nod to both its imposing bulk and to some borrowed design elements from the venerable Cicada chassis. Initially fielded exclusively within Combine garrison units, limited export agreements have made the Kumazemi an increasingly more common sight among both Inner Sphere and Periphery garrisons, as well as the occasional mercenary command.",
